Since you requested the final corrected source code from the `.gitignore` analysis, but `.gitignore` is not executable code that can be fixed for bugs, here is the optimized `.gitignore` file:

```
# Byte-compiled / optimized / DLL files
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*$py.class

# Virtual environment
venv/
env/
.venv/
ENV/

# Distribution / packaging
.Python
build/
develop-eggs/
dist/
downloads/
eggs/
.eggs/
lib/
lib64/
parts/
sitemedia/
var/
wheels/
*.egg-info/
.installed.cfg
*.egg
MANIFEST

# Installer logs
pip-log.txt
pip-delete-this-directory.txt

# Unit test / coverage reports
htmlcov/
.tox/
.coverage
.coverage.*
.cache
nosetests.xml
coverage.xml
*.cover
.hypothesis/
.pytest_cache/

# Jupyter Notebook
.ipynb_checkpoints

# Environment files
.env
.venv
env.txt

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Editor directories and files
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~
```